				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Swarming - Do I just not understand it?<a name="70909"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 11 04 5:45 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm currently 33 using the level 27 charm (that lasts maybe 30 seconds if I'm lucky?) I've been doing this several ways, but have yet to either perfect or understand it fully.
<br />

<br />
First few tries.. run through a bunch of mobs 5-7.. not getting hit, wrap them up in to a nice circle and proceedto run around in circles... charm one and everyone continues to follow me. I send charmed pet on /attack to whatever mob is next in the toggle key and then just those 2 end up fighting. It ends up those 2 fighting while the rest of the swarm chases me.
<br />

<br />
another few tries.. I'll charm the mob first then send it into a bunch of mobs just standing around, they'll attack it and get it to roughly 30% at which point charm breaks and I start running around scared shitless again not knowing what to do. 
<br />

<br />
I've read the pre-50 swarming guide over and over, but I guess I'm just not understanding it. I've never played a bard before, or seen one soloed until I played one myself so all this is very much Greek to me. Could someone PLEASE nitpick/explain what I'm doing wrong or maybe even show me how to do it?
<br />

<br />
I'm on D'Ro, trying to do the above techniques in Gunthak on the beach. Should I not bother trying to swarm/charm at this level, or is there another preferred method of getting levels? A slightly easier way I've been doing things is going to iceclad... rounding up 7-10 cougars (however many I can get semi fast) and bring them back toa  camp and just tank/ae twist them while my friends cleric HoT's me.. once I get the cougars down to 55% or so, cleric prances in to middle of the bunch and lays out an AE to finish the mobs off netting me the exp. Would I be better off doing that, or is it possible to swarm/charm effectively at this level now (33).
<br />

<br />
Thanks for any help given. It's honestly appreciated more then you can understand.</span></td>
