			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming - Do I just not understand it?<a name="70912"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 11 04 6:08 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The mobs have to be social first off.  Secondly, you need to restrict the number of mobs swarmed.  Only four mobs will assist, and usually, if the pet is the same type, only three will, forcing the last to go after you.  Thirdly, the only agro you get from the swarm is proximity agro.  Damage, usually via chants is saved for when the pet is almost road kill, breaking it as your pet before it dies (and praying the other mobs realize it is no longer your pet).  Don't worry though, once you get the hang of it, you'll have fun with it, as well as getting hit with the pet bug (assuming it is still present).  Any damage done to a mob in the swarm by you will cause the mob to always chase after you.  This is only a problem with full swarms or more as you can snare a single, allowing your pet to catch it.  Once the pet does enough damage, it will usually outagro your initial agro.  Also, if a full swarm, by constantly running the agro'd mob back through the mobs beating on your pet it is sometimes possible to loose agro due to low health agro from your pet.  However, upon killing the pet, the agro'd mob would usually wind up the next pet, but then can also introduce the pet bug.
<br />

<br />
Good luck with it.
<br />

<br />
Polara</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
