			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming - Do I just not understand it?<a name="70925"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 12 04 4:26 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Get a bunch of mobs  together. Charm one. Send it against a second mob. Once the pet gets aggro (usually just a hit or two) those two will stop. Now how the rest of your swarm reacts can be very different. Sometimes they will all attack your pet. This can vary with range to your pet and the pack and you, and how social they are. Usually at best the target and 3 other mobs will stop. The rest have to be kitted back over your pet for the pet to get aggro. Don't run directly over your pet though, you might get stunned and then the swarm can eat you, run around it keeping a good distance between you and the swarm then angle back so the swarm paths through the pet. 
<br />

<br />
The tricky part can be invising properly to break charm without getting your pet killed. Once it gets somewhat low hp start casting invis. Ideally the invis will cause the charm to break at 10% or less hp. Only experiance with the group of mobs you are kiting with will teach you when to start invising. Note that if you are standing still you can try to use hide to break charm if it looks like invis won't land in time but that can be tricky since its a skill and you won't always succeed. Once charm breaks you want to start running your swarm in circles as you single dot chant down your former pet till it is dead. 
<br />

<br />
Then use your previous target key to target the mob your pet was supposed to be attacking earlier and make a pet out if it. This way the mob that has the most residual hate built up against you is your pet (damage done by pet applies as aggro against the pets controller with charmed pets) and it won't chase you around like it might do if you don't charm it. This allows for easier kiting of the rest of the swarm. 
<br />

<br />
The huge advantage of swarm kiting over fear kiting is pure xp. It takes alot less time for 10 mobs to beat down 1 to near death letting you finish it off getting fulll xp then it does to beat one mob down that you are snaring/fearing. However fear kiting does let you build up your offensive melee skills without needing a group. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
