			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming - Do I just not understand it?<a name="70955"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 13 04 7:52 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Only four mobs will assist, and usually, if the pet is the same type, only three will, forcing the last to go after you.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Not so. I kite Hogobblins in PoN and I gather 9 of them, and they all agro on pet when I kite around the rest of them to where my pet is fighting the other mob I send it to.
<br />

<br />
When done with Hogobblins, they are not up so I agro all the Nettling Wraiths I can find (about 15 or so), plus one or 2 (sometimes 3) big mofo spiders (they proc FD on pet and I find it pretty funny, on top of dropping Nightmare Silks. Spiders are level 60). They all agro pet just the same as with Hogobblins (about 15-18 of them. I have to start invisibility as soon as they all agro and hit pet once), different mob types and all. In fact, I think different mob types works better for initial agro on pet, but if not, kiting around and leading them all to pet works just fine as well.
<br />

<br />
Hilbur nailed it. Do what Hilbur says. Also, level 39 charm last longer and will work better as spoogy said.
<br />

<br />
If I were you, I would go to South Karana and round up 4 or 5 gnolls to practice with. Practice Toggle key (as in, target mob, charm it, target another, send, hit toggle key so your pet HPs show, kite rest to pet, break charm with inv, chant it dead, Toggle-key for mob pet was hitting on to be on target, charm it,  wash, rinse, repeat). Practice charm-break-invisibility before mob dies. Practice zoning into Split Paw before dying  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Don&#180;t damage any mobs but the ex-pet you broke charm to kill with chants.
<br />

<br />
If charm breaks early and mob is at 40%+ as you say, just recharm it, send it to the same mob or different mob, kite rest around it to path thru pet, they should all reagro pet if you did no DMG to any of them (including the mob pet was hitting at), make sure you cast invisibility soon enough so pet doesn&#180;t die.
<br />

<br />
If you fumble targetting when charm breaks for whatever reason, just run backwards facing them and hit Cycle-NPC key (you have to set it up I think, as with Toggle-key), till you find the target you need, they will not catch you.
<br />

<br />
You will find Toggle-key very usufull for switching targets and mezzing while meleeing. Once a song is started, mez for instance, you can switch targets and it still land on the target you had when you started mez. 
<br />

<br />
Get a good drum (Thunderous Drum of Karana is great, but if none for sale or too expensive, Trueborn Drum of Dark Rites will do nicely also and should be fairly cheap), and GL to you. Charm kiting &gt; LFGing. In fact you can do both at the same time <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" /></span></td>
