				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming - Do I just not understand it?<a name="70963"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 13 04 11:07 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>First... Polara... 
<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Secondly, you need to restrict the number of mobs swarmed. Only four mobs will assist, and usually, if the pet is the same type, only three will, forcing the last to go after you.</span></blockquote>
<br />
This is pure drivel.  Not one bit of fact in that whole statement.  I have swarmed 30+, ALL FIGHTING, my preference is around 8 at a time.  Too high a number and the pet can die before I can reasonably break it.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Dont bother til 39. Charm duration is too short before then. Around level 41 hit Rathe Mts. Nice solo xp and plat</span></blockquote>
<br />
I could not disagree MORE.  Swarm kiting was BORN with the level 27 charm.  The level 39 charm was originally conceived by SOE/Verant as a NERF to swarm kiting.  Make it last longer and the bard will have to break it... make it take mana and they will have a limitation on how long they can do it.  It didn't work out that way.  I milked that mana-free charm until my targets were going light blue/green.  At that point you need to have some mana regen gear to swarm effectively.
<br />

<br />
The level 27 charm is GREAT for swarming.  You are only limited by how long you can run around without your wrist locking up.  Aim to have a swarm that will nearly kill your target at the point the charm breaks naturally.  This will be the most efficient.  
<br />

<br />
For the rest... Hilbur was pretty much right on the money
<br />

<br />
Reys</span></td>
