			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming - Do I just not understand it?<a name="70998"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 14 04 10:14 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">once the &quot;pet&quot; is low on hp chant it down or charm another mob to kill the former pet/also doing dmg so the mob won't poof) </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I would suggest not charming another and having it attack yoru former pet. Once the charm breaks on the former pet, damage done is nulled out. That's why when you chant it down, you get the experience for the kill instead of it just poofing like if the swarm kills it. If you charm a new pet and sic it on the former pet, it's a race between your damage and the new pets damage. There's an inverse relation between how much damage a charmed pet does and how much experience you get for the kill. The more damage a charmed pet does, the less experience you get. I would suggest you just chant the former pet down for now on.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
