			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming - Do I just not understand it?<a name="71115"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 15 04 10:42 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Remember that proximity plays a part too. If you run the swarm over your pet but stop 5 feet from him, they're going to chase you. Use your speed to your advantage. Run a semi wide half circle to get some distance on them, then run past your pet and angle the swarms approach to run over him. As long as you got enough distance and haven't done anything to over aggro (charming different mobs by accident or mezzing or whatever; you should ONLY use proximity aggro to gather your swarm) they should stick to your pet without much trouble.
<br />

<br />
EDIT: Also, make sure you're not playing any songs as the swarm gets close to your pet. This will generate extra aggro on you (it's very little, but often times just enough to keep their attention on you).</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1003866"> <img src="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/uf/Jiggidyjay/zingsig.jpg"></a></br><fontsize=8>Zingin Ansinging, Povar</fontsize></span></td>
